MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Symbols' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Symbols Thin'.

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Symbols' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Symbols Light'.

Noto Sans Symbols Bold (NotoSansSymbols-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansSymbols-Bold', Everything looks good.

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Symbols ExtraBold' ≠ 'Noto Sans Symbols ExtBd' (NID 1).

Noto Sans Symbols Blk Regular (NotoSansSymbols-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Symbols Black' ≠ 'Noto Sans Symbols Blk' (NID 1).
